The comedy shows are awesome! They bring in a lot of talent. The food is pretty good, too. My only gripe is with the beer. Don't get me wrong, the selection is alright, and so is everything that comes in a can or a bottle. However, for whatever reason, the stuff they have on tap is always a bit watery and musky. Aside from that, this place is great, and I highly recommend that you check it out!

Amazing food for a "bar" I had the steak and cheese and roasted brussel sprouts. Went for the comedy night, well worth the price. Show up 30 minutes early for good seats. Don't hesitate on getting tickets as day of the show it typically sells out

I was extremely disappointed and disgusted with the alcohol they served. I had a few drinks and each time requested to have Smirnoff in it. The bartender informed me that they were out of it and was putting a no name with no label alcohol in the drink. When I asked what it was he simply replied "vodka". The vodka they serve is cheap and poor quality. I felt bad during the night, threw up and woke up in the morning with a bad hangover.
